{"word":"γονή","slug":"γονή","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>γονή</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γίγνομαι'><el>γίγνομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>produce, offspring</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; so in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>like <el>γενεά, γένος</el>, <i>a race, stock, family</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a generation</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>that which engenders, the seed</i>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the womb</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b>of the mother, <i>child-birth</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of the child, <i>birth</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}